WEBVTT

00:04.588 --> 00:06.214
>> HUMANS CALL THAT BRIGHT ONE

00:06.340 --> 00:07.174
THE NORTH STAR.

00:07.299 --> 00:08.968
>> AND THE SMALLER STAR NEXT TO

00:09.092 --> 00:09.927
IT?

00:10.051 --> 00:11.094
>> I'M NOT SURE THAT ONE HAS A

00:11.219 --> 00:12.053
NAME.

00:12.179 --> 00:13.430
>> NOBODY EVER PAYS ATTENTION TO

00:13.555 --> 00:14.515
THE LITTLE GUYS.

00:14.640 --> 00:16.266
>> IT MAY BE LITTLE, BUT IT'S

00:16.391 --> 00:18.769
STILL A STAR.

00:18.894 --> 00:19.645
>> LOOK AT THAT.

00:19.770 --> 00:20.771
>> DID YOU SEE THAT?

00:20.896 --> 00:21.522
>> WHOA.

00:21.647 --> 00:23.022
WHAT STAR IS THAT?

00:23.148 --> 00:24.817
>> IT'S NOT A STAR.

00:24.942 --> 00:26.777
THAT'S A METEOR -- HEADED

00:26.902 --> 00:28.445
STRAIGHT FOR WAYWARD ISLAND.

00:28.570 --> 00:30.531
GOOD THING NO ONE LIVES THERE.

00:35.577 --> 00:37.245
WELL, I KNOW WHAT WE'RE DOING

00:37.371 --> 00:39.331
TOMORROW.

00:49.048 --> 00:50.968
[ WATER SLOSHING ]

00:54.638 --> 00:56.181
>> I'VE NEVER SEEN A METEOR UP

00:56.306 --> 00:57.725
CLOSE -- OR AT  ALL,  FOR THAT

00:57.850 --> 00:58.642
MATTER.

00:58.767 --> 00:59.852
>> IT'S TOO BAD DOC GREENE'S

00:59.977 --> 01:01.520
AWAY ON THE MAINLAND FOR A FEW

01:01.645 --> 01:02.187
DAYS.

01:02.312 --> 01:02.980
HE'D LOVE THIS.

01:03.146 --> 01:04.231
>> TEAM, WE NEED TO FIND

01:04.356 --> 01:05.649
PRECISELY WHERE THAT METEOR

01:05.774 --> 01:07.275
LANDED AND MAKE SURE IT DOESN'T

01:07.401 --> 01:08.861
PRESENT ANY KIND OF HAZARD.

01:08.986 --> 01:09.820
[ OWL HOOTS ]

01:09.945 --> 01:11.739
>> AND, UH, LET'S MAKE IT QUICK,

01:11.864 --> 01:12.740
HUH?

01:12.865 --> 01:14.700
THIS PLACE GIVES ME THE CREEPS.

01:29.130 --> 01:31.050
[ WHOOSH ]

01:34.428 --> 01:35.136
[ WHOOSH ]

01:35.262 --> 01:37.056
>> SHH. SOMEONE'S HERE.

01:43.520 --> 01:45.856
[ ALL GASP ]

01:49.317 --> 01:51.194
>> ♪ A ROUTINE PATROL WITH FOUR

01:51.319 --> 01:52.112
BOTS IN STASIS ♪

01:52.237 --> 01:53.447
♪ YEARS LATER, AWOKE IN THE

01:53.572 --> 01:54.990
STRANGEST OF PLACES ♪

01:55.115 --> 01:56.575
♪ EARTH WAS THEIR HOME NOW, AND

01:56.700 --> 01:57.576
IN ADDITION ♪

01:57.701 --> 01:59.160
>> ♪ OPTIMUS PRIME GAVE THEM

01:59.286 --> 02:00.161
THIS MISSION ♪

02:00.287 --> 02:01.288
>> ♪ LEARN FROM THE HUMANS,

02:01.413 --> 02:02.623
SERVE AND PROTECT ♪

02:02.748 --> 02:04.207
♪ LIVE IN THEIR WORLD, EARN

02:04.332 --> 02:05.125
THEIR RESPECT ♪

02:05.250 --> 02:07.127
♪ A FAMILY OF HEROES WILL BE

02:07.252 --> 02:08.087
YOUR ALLIES ♪

02:08.211 --> 02:09.755
♪ TO OTHERS, REMAIN ROBOTS IN

02:09.880 --> 02:10.589
DISGUISE ♪

02:10.714 --> 02:11.673
>> ♪ RESCUE BOTS ♪

02:11.799 --> 02:13.092
>> ♪ ROLL TO THE RESCUE ♪

02:13.216 --> 02:14.093
>> ♪ HUMANS IN NEED ♪

02:14.217 --> 02:15.677
>> ♪ HEROES, INDEED ♪

02:15.803 --> 02:16.720
>> ♪ RESCUE BOTS ♪

02:16.845 --> 02:18.305
>> ♪ ROLL TO THE RESCUE ♪

02:18.430 --> 02:20.849
>> ♪ RESCUE BOTS ♪

02:27.064 --> 02:28.899
>> ANOTHER BOT?

02:29.024 --> 02:31.110
>> AND HE'S YELLOW!

02:31.234 --> 02:32.111
NOBLE.

02:32.235 --> 02:34.362
>> IT'S -- IT'S BUMBLEBEE.

02:34.488 --> 02:36.115
IT'S AN HONOR.

02:36.239 --> 02:37.866
I'M HEATWAVE.

02:37.992 --> 02:38.700
>> BOULDER.

02:38.826 --> 02:39.952
>> AND I AM CHASE.

02:40.077 --> 02:41.829
WE HAVE ALL HEARD MANY STORIES

02:41.954 --> 02:42.621
ABOUT YOU.

02:42.746 --> 02:44.498
>> [ BUZZING ]

02:44.623 --> 02:46.500
>> UH, BLADES, YOU WANT TO FILL

02:46.625 --> 02:48.335
US IN ON YOUR BEEPING BUDDY?

02:48.460 --> 02:49.878
>> BUMBLEBEE IS PART OF

02:50.004 --> 02:51.338
OPTIMUS PRIME'S TEAM.

02:51.463 --> 02:53.048
HE'S A LEGENDARY SCOUT AND

02:53.172 --> 02:54.133
SOLDIER AND...

02:54.257 --> 02:55.717
>> [ BUZZING ]

02:55.843 --> 02:57.011
>> HOW DO YOU DO?

02:57.136 --> 02:58.137
I'M BUMBLEBEE.

02:58.261 --> 03:00.097
NO, I MEAN,  YOU'RE  BUMBLEBEE.

03:00.221 --> 03:02.016
I'M...

03:02.141 --> 03:03.517
>> BLADES.

03:03.642 --> 03:04.726
>> ...BLADES.

03:04.852 --> 03:06.394
IT'S TRULY AN HONOR.

03:06.520 --> 03:07.354
>> [ CHUCKLES ]

03:07.479 --> 03:08.730
SOMEONE'S A LITTLE STARSTRUCK,

03:08.856 --> 03:10.357
HUH?

03:10.482 --> 03:12.901
>> [ BUZZING ]

03:15.737 --> 03:17.531
>> BUMBLEBEE LOST HIS VOICEBOX

03:17.656 --> 03:18.866
IN THE LINE OF DUTY.

03:18.991 --> 03:20.742
>> [ BUZZING ]

03:20.868 --> 03:22.536
>> HE SAYS HE WAS TRACKING THE

03:22.661 --> 03:23.537
METEOR.

03:23.662 --> 03:25.039
WHEN HE SAW IT LAND SO CLOSE TO

03:25.164 --> 03:26.915
GRIFFIN ROCK, HE DECIDED TO PAY

03:27.041 --> 03:28.625
A VISIT AND HELP US CHECK IT

03:28.750 --> 03:29.668
OUT.

03:29.793 --> 03:32.295
>> [ BUZZING ]

03:32.420 --> 03:34.131
>> THE PLEASURE'S OURS.

03:34.255 --> 03:36.550
>> WELCOME TO THE TEAM, MR. BEE.

03:36.675 --> 03:39.594
>> [ BUZZING ]

03:39.720 --> 03:41.138
>> BUMBLEBEE WAS HEADED UP TO

03:41.262 --> 03:41.972
THE RIDGE.

03:42.097 --> 03:43.098
HE SAW SOME TREES DOWN,

03:43.223 --> 03:44.725
INDICATING WHERE THE METEOR MAY

03:44.850 --> 03:45.475
HAVE LANDED.

03:45.600 --> 03:46.601
>> GOOD CALL.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.145
THE REST OF US WILL SPREAD OUT

03:48.269 --> 03:49.479
DOWN HERE IN THE VALLEY.

03:49.604 --> 03:50.981
BLADES, DANI, PUT EYES IN THE

03:51.106 --> 03:51.940
AIR.

03:52.066 --> 03:53.441
STAY ON YOUR COMMS, EVERYONE.

04:00.074 --> 04:01.700
>> WHOA!

04:01.825 --> 04:03.618
WATCH THE TREETOPS.

04:03.744 --> 04:04.745
>> SORRY.

04:04.870 --> 04:06.163
I'M JUST SO EXCITED.

04:06.287 --> 04:08.289
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M ON A MISSION

04:08.415 --> 04:09.666
WITH  THE  BUMBLEBEE.

04:09.791 --> 04:10.584
>> [ CHUCKLES ]

04:10.709 --> 04:11.835
BLADES, WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE

04:11.960 --> 04:12.961
SEARCHING FOR A METEOR,

04:13.087 --> 04:13.587
REMEMBER?

04:13.712 --> 04:14.504
>> THE METEOR?

04:14.629 --> 04:15.630
OH, IT'S RIGHT DOWN THERE --

04:15.756 --> 04:17.716
STARBOARD, 40 DEGREES.

04:20.677 --> 04:21.678
>> DAD, FOUND IT.

04:21.803 --> 04:23.471
DOWN IN THE CLEARING NEAR THE

04:23.597 --> 04:24.472
LAGOON.

04:24.598 --> 04:25.807
I'M NOT SURE WE CAN LAND THERE.

04:25.933 --> 04:27.226
IT'S A PRETTY DENSE AREA.

04:27.350 --> 04:28.476
>> No. Don't risk it.

04:28.602 --> 04:29.561
We'll find the rock.

04:29.686 --> 04:31.063
Blades, please let Bumblebee

04:31.188 --> 04:32.064
know where we are.

04:32.189 --> 04:34.942
>> YOU WANT ME TO...TALK TO HIM?

04:35.067 --> 04:37.027
OKAY!

04:44.701 --> 04:45.869
>> BETTER LET US TAKE A LOOK

04:45.994 --> 04:46.828
FIRST, CHIEF.

04:46.954 --> 04:47.955
MIGHT HAVE PICKED UP SOMETHING

04:48.080 --> 04:49.164
IN SPACE THAT'S HARMFUL TO

04:49.289 --> 04:51.208
HUMANS.

05:07.474 --> 05:09.601
>> NO TRACE OF RADIATION OR

05:09.726 --> 05:11.061
GAMMA PARTICLES.

05:11.186 --> 05:14.564
>> YOU MAY SAFELY APPROACH.

05:14.689 --> 05:18.568
[ HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING ]

05:18.693 --> 05:20.361
>> LET'S GIVE BUMBLEBEE A RIDE.

05:20.487 --> 05:21.905
>> WE CAN'T GO DOWN THERE,

05:22.030 --> 05:22.739
BLADES.

05:22.864 --> 05:23.991
THERE ARE TOO MANY TREES.

05:24.116 --> 05:26.493
>> I CAN MAKE IT.

05:26.618 --> 05:28.245
BUMBLEBEE, GRAB ONTO MY

05:28.369 --> 05:29.204
WING AND --

05:29.329 --> 05:31.539
AAH! AAH! AAH!

05:31.665 --> 05:33.292
>> [ GRUNTS ]

05:33.416 --> 05:34.001
>> WHOA!

05:34.126 --> 05:36.419
>> [ BUZZES ]

05:36.544 --> 05:38.964
>> I'M...CAUGHT!

05:39.089 --> 05:40.174
[ GRUNTS ]

05:40.299 --> 05:42.259
>> [ BUZZING ]

05:46.471 --> 05:47.681
>> WOW.

05:47.806 --> 05:49.516
>> I CAN'T BELIEVE I DID THAT.

05:49.641 --> 05:51.268
MY ONE CHANCE TO WORK WITH A

05:51.392 --> 05:52.144
LEGEND.

05:52.269 --> 05:55.856
>> [ BUZZING ]

05:55.981 --> 05:57.149
>> WHAT'D HE SAY?

05:57.274 --> 05:58.650
>> [ SIGHS ]

05:58.775 --> 06:01.195
"SOME DAYS, YOU DO THE RESCUING.

06:01.320 --> 06:03.404
SOME DAYS, YOU GET RESCUED."

06:05.740 --> 06:07.201
>> THE METEOR APPEARS TO HAVE

06:07.326 --> 06:08.869
ORIGINATED WITHIN EARTH'S SOLAR

06:08.994 --> 06:09.870
SYSTEM.

06:09.995 --> 06:11.079
>> LET'S MAKE SURE THERE ARE NO

06:11.205 --> 06:12.497
MORE FIRES, THEN HEAD OUT.

06:12.622 --> 06:14.166
I WANT TO GET A HEAD START ON

06:14.291 --> 06:15.083
THIS STORM.

06:15.209 --> 06:16.626
>> DANI, WE'RE ALL DONE DOWN

06:16.751 --> 06:17.376
HERE.

06:17.502 --> 06:18.337
WHAT'S YOUR STATUS?

06:18.461 --> 06:19.504
>> Uh, sorry, guys.

06:19.629 --> 06:21.215
We were...caught up in things.

06:21.340 --> 06:23.300
Meet you at the boat.

06:28.638 --> 06:33.518
>> [ BUZZING ]

06:33.643 --> 06:36.146
>> YES...I THINK.

06:36.271 --> 06:38.106
CAN BUMBLEBEE COME BACK WITH US?

06:38.232 --> 06:39.900
HE WANTS TO USE OUR COMM SCREEN

06:40.025 --> 06:41.735
TO CHECK IN WITH OPTIMUS PRIME.

06:41.860 --> 06:42.819
>> OF COURSE.

06:42.944 --> 06:44.112
GLAD TO HAVE YOU.

06:44.238 --> 06:45.113
>> CHECK IN?

06:45.239 --> 06:46.865
OPTIMUS  IS  AWARE OF YOUR

06:46.990 --> 06:48.616
PRESENCE HERE, IS HE NOT?

06:48.742 --> 06:51.494
>> [ BUZZING ]

06:51.619 --> 06:54.206
>> HE SAYS, "NOT EXACTLY."

06:54.331 --> 06:57.918
>> THANKS. I GOT THAT ONE.

06:58.043 --> 06:59.669
>>  WHILE I APPRECIATE YOUR

06:59.794 --> 07:01.629
DESIRE TO HELP, BUMBLEBEE, I

07:01.755 --> 07:03.715
CANNOT CONDONE YOU UNDERTAKING

07:03.840 --> 07:05.842
A MISSION WITHOUT MY KNOWLEDG.

07:05.967 --> 07:07.969
I AM, HOWEVER, GLAD TO HEAR

07:08.095 --> 07:09.930
THAT THE METEOR YOU FOUND

07:10.055 --> 07:12.182
APPEARS TO BE NONTHREATENING.

07:12.307 --> 07:14.142
THANK YOU, RESCUE BOTS, FOR

07:14.268 --> 07:15.143
YOUR HELP.

07:15.269 --> 07:16.978
BUMBLEBEE, I SUGGEST YOU SPEND

07:17.104 --> 07:18.939
A FEW MORE DAYS WITH THE RESCE

07:19.064 --> 07:19.856
TEAM.

07:19.981 --> 07:21.233
OBSERVE HOW THEY WORK WITH

07:21.358 --> 07:23.526
THEIR HUMAN PARTNERS AND WITH

07:23.651 --> 07:24.945
EACH OTHER.

07:25.070 --> 07:26.071
>> AHEM.

07:26.196 --> 07:28.990
OPTIMUS, SIR, IF ANY OPENINGS

07:29.116 --> 07:30.367
COME UP ON YOUR TEAM...

07:30.491 --> 07:32.119
>>  THANK YOU FOR YOUR CONTINUED

07:32.244 --> 07:33.328
INTEREST, HEATWAVE.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.623
RESCUE BOTS, GOOD LUCK.

07:38.750 --> 07:39.500
>> [ SIGHS ]

07:39.626 --> 07:41.295
>> WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE TO DO

07:41.420 --> 07:42.254
FIRST?

07:42.379 --> 07:45.257
WATCH SOME TV OR, UM, KARAOKE?

07:45.382 --> 07:46.425
>> I HAVE A WORKOUT AREA.

07:46.549 --> 07:47.717
HOW ABOUT A LITTLE SPARRING,

07:47.842 --> 07:48.551
BEE?

07:48.676 --> 07:49.510
>> PERHAPS YOU WOULD BE

07:49.636 --> 07:50.553
INTERESTED IN HOW HUMANS HAVE

07:50.678 --> 07:51.763
CODIFIED ILLEGAL BEHAVIOR.

07:51.888 --> 07:53.181
459 MEANS BURGLARY.

07:53.307 --> 07:54.933
494 -- GENERAL MISCHIEF.

07:55.058 --> 07:57.394
263 -- DANCING WITHOUT A PERMIT.

07:57.518 --> 07:59.104
>> HOW ABOUT AN ARCHITECTURAL

07:59.229 --> 08:00.355
TOUR OF GRIFFIN ROCK?

08:00.521 --> 08:01.773
THE SHINGLE STYLE IS MY

08:01.898 --> 08:02.732
FAVORITE.

08:02.857 --> 08:04.192
>> YOU WANT TO SEE MY GO-KART?

08:04.318 --> 08:04.943
[ BEEP ]

08:05.068 --> 08:05.860
>>  EMERGENCY, TEAM.

08:05.986 --> 08:07.237
THE RETAINING WALL BEING

08:07.362 --> 08:08.905
REPAIRED ALONG THE OLD ROAD HS

08:09.030 --> 08:10.073
STARTED TO GIVE OUT.

08:10.198 --> 08:11.283
IF IT'S NOT SHORED UP

08:11.408 --> 08:12.575
IMMEDIATELY, THE ENTIRE

08:12.700 --> 08:14.077
MOUNTAINSIDE COULD GIVE WAY

08:14.202 --> 08:15.912
ONTO THE HOUSES BELOW.

08:16.037 --> 08:17.705
>> THIS IS A PERFECT CHANCE FOR

08:17.831 --> 08:19.458
YOU TO SEE WHAT WE CAN DO!

08:19.582 --> 08:20.834
>>  BEST IF BUMBLEBEE WATCHES

08:20.959 --> 08:22.336
FROM THE STATION WITH CODY FOR

08:22.461 --> 08:23.253
NOW.

08:23.378 --> 08:24.254
MIGHT BE HARD TO EXPLAIN A

08:24.379 --> 08:26.214
BRAND-NEW BOT ON GRIFFIN ROCK.

08:36.183 --> 08:37.892
>> RESCUE BOTS, ROLL TO THE

08:38.018 --> 08:38.726
RESCUE.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.770
[ SIREN WAILS ]

08:47.027 --> 08:48.945
[ ALL GRUNT ]

08:53.408 --> 08:54.784
>> A FEW GIRDERS IN THE RIGHT

08:54.909 --> 08:56.453
PLACES SHOULD SHORE UP THE WALL

08:56.577 --> 08:58.079
UNTIL IT CAN BE FULLY REBUILT.

08:58.205 --> 09:01.333
BOULDER?

09:01.458 --> 09:03.751
>> [ BUZZING ]

09:03.877 --> 09:04.961
>> I-I'M SORRY.

09:05.086 --> 09:07.464
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

09:07.588 --> 09:08.507
>> [ BUZZES ]

09:08.631 --> 09:09.424
>> OH. YEAH!

09:09.549 --> 09:10.967
THEY MAKE A GREAT TEAM.

09:11.092 --> 09:12.552
>>  AAH!

09:14.804 --> 09:16.097
>> WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:16.223 --> 09:17.349
>> I DON'T KNOW.

09:17.474 --> 09:19.226
I-I FELT A TWINGE, AND THEN I

09:19.351 --> 09:21.144
WENT INTO VEHICLE MODE WITHOUT

09:21.269 --> 09:22.979
EVEN TRYING TO.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.689
>> WELL, CHANGE BACK.

09:24.814 --> 09:26.149
>> COME ON, BOULDER.

09:26.274 --> 09:28.151
WE CAN'T HOLD THIS THING...

09:28.276 --> 09:30.778
AAH!

09:30.904 --> 09:33.448
>> WHAT'S HAPPENING?

09:33.573 --> 09:35.534
>> WHATEVER IT IS, I FEAR THAT

09:35.658 --> 09:36.159
IT...

09:36.284 --> 09:37.785
[ GRUNTS ]

09:37.911 --> 09:40.121
>> [ GRUNTING ]

09:40.247 --> 09:42.916
UM...GUYS?

09:43.041 --> 09:44.959
A LITTLE HELP?

09:47.504 --> 09:49.381
[ RUMBLING ]

09:49.506 --> 09:52.800
>> [ GRUNTS ]

09:52.926 --> 09:54.844
[ ALL GRUNT ]

09:57.514 --> 09:59.099
>> NOT ENOUGH TIME TO EVACUATE

09:59.224 --> 10:01.935
THOSE HOMES.

10:02.060 --> 10:04.104
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

10:04.229 --> 10:05.688
>> DAD, BUMBLEBEE AND I ARE

10:05.813 --> 10:06.356
EN ROUTE.

10:06.481 --> 10:07.566
I COULDN'T STOP HIM.

10:07.690 --> 10:08.900
>> IT'S ALL RIGHT, SON.

10:09.025 --> 10:10.610
RIGHT NOW, WE COULD DEFINITELY

10:10.735 --> 10:12.153
USE THE HELP.

10:12.279 --> 10:13.447
>> [ GRUNTS ]

10:13.572 --> 10:15.698
YOU ALL BETTER STAND BACK.

10:15.823 --> 10:17.700
NOT SURE HOW MUCH LONGER I

10:17.825 --> 10:21.204
CAN...

10:21.329 --> 10:23.748
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

10:23.873 --> 10:25.833
[ ENGINE REVS ]

10:33.967 --> 10:37.095
[ GRUNTS ]

10:37.220 --> 10:39.139
>> [ BUZZING ]

10:42.058 --> 10:44.269
>> I GUESS TODAY'S MY DAY TO BE

10:44.394 --> 10:46.313
RESCUED TWICE.

10:48.731 --> 10:51.067
>> GUYS! WHAT HAPPENED?

10:51.192 --> 10:52.569
>> [ SIGHS ] WISH I KNEW.

10:52.693 --> 10:53.945
>> LET'S HEAD BACK TO THE

10:54.070 --> 10:54.821
STATION.

10:54.946 --> 10:56.448
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT THERE.

10:56.573 --> 10:58.283
>> BLADES, IF YOU AND BUMBLEBEE

10:58.408 --> 11:00.118
DON'T MIND, THIS WALL COULD USE

11:00.243 --> 11:02.287
A FEW MORE GIRDERS.

11:02.412 --> 11:04.331
>> [ BUZZING ]

11:07.792 --> 11:09.252
>> ANY TIME YOU'RE READY,

11:09.377 --> 11:10.253
PARTNER.

11:10.378 --> 11:11.838
>> I AM SORRY TO REPORT, CHIEF,

11:11.963 --> 11:13.798
THAT I AM UNABLE TO MOVE MYSELF

11:13.923 --> 11:15.592
VEHICULARLY IN ANY DIRECTION.

11:15.716 --> 11:18.512
PERHAPS IF YOU PUT YOUR FOOT ON

11:18.637 --> 11:19.887
MY GAS PEDAL?

11:20.013 --> 11:21.931
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

11:24.434 --> 11:25.435
>> HEATWAVE?

11:25.560 --> 11:27.770
>> HATE TO ADMIT IT, BUT LOOKS

11:27.895 --> 11:30.190
LIKE  YOU'RE  IN CONTROL.

11:30.315 --> 11:32.150
>> ON THE BRIGHT SIDE, THIS IS A

11:32.275 --> 11:34.235
COMPLETELY NEW EXPERIENCE.

11:37.447 --> 11:38.865
>> [ SIGHS ]

11:38.990 --> 11:41.368
ALL I WANT IS A CHANCE TO PROVE

11:41.493 --> 11:43.119
MYSELF TO BUMBLEBEE.

11:43.244 --> 11:45.497
>> YOU DID YOUR BEST, BLADES.

11:45.622 --> 11:47.248
BESIDES, COUNT YOUR BLESSINGS.

11:47.374 --> 11:48.833
YOU'RE NOT FROZEN IN VEHICLE

11:48.958 --> 11:49.334
MODE.

11:49.459 --> 11:50.335
>> HEH.

11:50.460 --> 11:51.961
NOW, THIS IS THE WAY IT  SHOULD

11:52.086 --> 11:52.879
BE.

11:53.004 --> 11:54.381
I TURN THE WHEEL, YOU MOVE.

11:54.506 --> 11:56.174
>> DON'T GET COMFORTABLE.

11:56.299 --> 11:59.093
AS SOON AS WE FIND OUT WHAT --

11:59.219 --> 12:00.637
>> WHAT -- THAT I'M A BETTER

12:00.761 --> 12:01.638
DRIVER THAN YOU?

12:01.762 --> 12:02.430
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:02.556 --> 12:03.515
HEATWAVE?

12:03.640 --> 12:05.600
HEATWAVE?

12:09.646 --> 12:11.481
>> MORE BAD NEWS, I'M AFRAID.

12:11.606 --> 12:13.525
>> THEY CAN'T EVEN TALK NOW.

